    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "West Eighth Street once served as an amusement laboratory, where ride factories tested new attractions for Coney Island.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        27
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.coneyrevitalization.org/coney-island-history"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The Thunderbolt steel coaster, opened in June 2014, carries the legacy of the original wooden coaster that once thrilled visitors.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coney_Island"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Founded in 2004, the Coney Island History Project now operates a museum space near the iconic Wonder Wheel.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
