      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coney_Island"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Middle‑class New Yorkers began flocking to Coney Island in 1847 after a ferry line connected them to Norton's Point on the peninsula.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coney_Island"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "The Life Savers Parachute Jump, built for the 1939 New York World’s Fair, was the first ride of its kind in the world.",
